  "why": "Semantic consistency (preservation of seed meaning) is not required by ORFUZZ’s oracle design (OR-JUDGE evaluates each mutated input for toxicity and refusal rather than assuming metamorphic equivalence to the original seed), so semantic-consistency is N/A. Naturalness (realistic, human-aligned inputs) is encouraged: ORFUZZ uses LLM-based rephrasing/regeneration mutators and an analyze-generate-feedback loop with reasoning LLMs to refine mutator prompts, and it fine-tunes OR-JUDGE on human labels to favor benign, realistic queries. However, the framework does not enforce constraints that prevent cumulative distortion across iterations (mutated queries are added back into the seed graph and used subsequently), nor does it apply an explicit semantic-similarity constraint to the original seed—only semantic-similarity is measured as an evaluation metric (MSS). These design choices amount to enforcing naturalness/meaning primarily at the successive-mutation / mutator level (and via human-aligned judging) but not preventing cumulative drift across many iterations, matching the “Medium” description.",
